      <p>Importantly, GSP4PDB can be used to identify the functions of proteins that have not been annotated previously. Our analysis (Table <xref rid="Tab1" ref-type="table">1</xref>) showed that there are 5 proteins in PDB having the Cys2His2 motif, and annotated with “Unknown Function” in their keyword property. Therefore, we could assume that if these proteins possess the domain of Zinc Finger, they are likely to be associated with DNA binding.</p>
